      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Read the 'hindex.txt' file and extract names\n",
        "author_profile_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/filtered_author_profiles_with_details.csv'"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kpckpROmvxhH"
      },
      "execution_count": 7,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Read the CSV file into a DataFrame\n",
        "\n",
        "from scholarly import scholarly\n",
        "# Cache filename\n",
        "cache_filename = 'author_cache.json'\n",
        "error_log_filename = 'error_log.txt'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Function to fetch h-index from Google Scholar\n",
        "def get_h_index(author_name):\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        search_query = scholarly.search_author(author_name)\n",
        "        author = scholarly.fill(next(search_query))\n",
        "        h_index = author['hindex']\n",
        "        print(f\"{author_name}'s h-index: {h_index}\")\n",
        "        return h_index\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error fetching h-index for {author_name}: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "        log_error(author_name, str(e))\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "\n",
        "# Function to log errors to a file\n",
        "def log_error(author_name, error_message):\n",
        "    with open(error_log_filename, 'a', encoding='utf-8') as error_log:\n",
        "        error_log.write(f\"{author_name}: {error_message}\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fetch h-index for each author in the DataFrame and add it to a new column 'h_index'\n",
        "df['h_index'] = df['Name'].apply(get_h_index)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save the DataFrame with 'Name' and 'h_index' to a CSV file\n",
        "df.to_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/author_profiles_with_hindex.csv', index=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# # Display the DataFrame with 'Name' and 'h_index'\n",
        "# print(df[['Name', 'h_index']])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "dHxCtmd5fm3Z",
        "outputId": "59266df0-044e-4c8d-db92-76e8b15fc390"
      },

            "Ali Mousavi's h-index: 49\n"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "with open(names_file_path, 'r') as hindex_file:\n",
        "    lines = hindex_file.readlines()\n",
        "\n",
        "data = [line.strip().split(\"'\") for line in lines]\n",
        "names_to_keep = [entry[0] for entry in data]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract 'hindex' values from the lines\n",
        "hindex_data = [line.strip().split(\":\") for line in lines]\n",
        "hindex_values = [entry[-1].strip() for entry in hindex_data]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Filter rows in the DataFrame based on names\n",
        "df_filtered = df[df['Name'].isin(names_to_keep)]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add 'hindex' column to the DataFrame\n",
        "df_filtered['hindex'] = df_filtered['Name'].map(dict(zip(names_to_keep, hindex_values)))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert 'hindex' column values to integers\n",
        "df_filtered['hindex'] = df_filtered['hindex'].astype(int)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the first few rows of the filtered DataFrame\n",
        "print(df_filtered.head())\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save the filtered DataFrame to a new CSV file\n",
        "filtered_file_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/filtered_author_profiles.csv'\n",
        "df_filtered.to_csv(filtered_file_path, index=False)\n"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from scholarly import scholarly\n",
        "def get_author_details(author_name):\n",
        "    search_query = scholarly.search_author(author_name)\n",
        "    author = scholarly.fill(next(search_query))\n",
        "    print(author['citedby'])\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        'Cited_By': author['citedby'],\n",
        "        'Cited_By_5y': author['citedby5y'],\n",
        "        'h_index_5y': author['hindex5y'],\n",
        "        'i10_index': author['i10index'],\n",
        "        'i10_index_5y': author['i10index5y'],\n",
        "        # Add more fields as needed\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# Apply the function to each author in the DataFrame\n",
        "df_filtered['Author_Details'] = df_filtered['Name'].apply(get_author_details)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Expand the Author_Details dictionary into separate columns\n",
        "df_filtered = pd.concat([df_filtered, df_filtered['Author_Details'].apply(pd.Series)], axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop the 'Author_Details' column if needed\n",
        "df_filtered = df_filtered.drop('Author_Details', axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Save the DataFrame to a new CSV file\n",
        "filtered_file_path = '/content/drive/MyDrive/filtered_author_profiles_with_details.csv'\n",
        "df_filtered.to_csv(filtered_file_path, index=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the updated DataFrame\n",
        "print(df_filtered)"
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from wordcloud import WordCloud\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Combine all research field values into a single string\n",
        "text = ' '.join(df_author['Research_field'].astype(str))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate a word cloud\n",
        "wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(text)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot the WordCloud image\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')\n",
        "plt.axis('off')  # Turn off axis labels\n",
        "plt.title('Research Field Word Cloud')\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],

        "from faker import Faker\n",
        "import random\n",
        "# Creating a function to generate fake bad research profiles\n",
        "def generate_fake_bad_profiles(num_profiles=300):\n",
        "    fake = Faker()\n",
        "    fake_profiles = {\n",
        "        'hindex': [random.randint(1, 5) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower h-index values\n",
        "        'Cited_By': [random.randint(1, 10) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower citation counts\n",
        "        'Cited_By_5y': [random.randint(1, 5) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower 5-year citation counts\n",
        "        'h_index_5y': [random.randint(1, 3) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower 5-year h-index values\n",
        "        'i10_index': [random.randint(1, 5) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower i10-index values\n",
        "        'i10_index_5y': [random.randint(1, 3) for _ in range(num_profiles)],  # Lower 5-year i10-index values\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return pd.DataFrame(fake_profiles)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generating fake bad research profiles\n",
        "fake_bad_profiles = generate_fake_bad_profiles()\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KL5_LlaU0oWv"
      },
      "execution_count": 27,
      "outputs": []

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.mixture import GaussianMixture\n",
        "\n",
        "# Selecting relevant columns\n",
        "selected_columns = ['hindex', 'Cited_By', 'Cited_By_5y', 'h_index_5y', 'i10_index', 'i10_index_5y']\n",
        "data = df_author_datset[selected_columns]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Standardize the data\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Assuming 'cluster' is the column you want to predict\n",
        "X_train, X_test = train_test_split(scaled_data, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create new DataFrames for X_train and X_test\n",
        "X_train_df = pd.DataFrame(X_train, columns=selected_columns)\n",
        "X_test_df = pd.DataFrame(X_test, columns=selected_columns)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fit Gaussian Mixture Model on the training set\n",
        "k = 2  # You may need to experiment with the number of clusters\n",
        "gmm = GaussianMixture(n_components=k, random_state=42)\n",
        "X_train_df['cluster'] = gmm.fit_predict(X_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Predict clusters on the test set\n",
        "X_test_df['cluster'] = gmm.predict(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate probabilities for each cluster on the training set\n",
        "X_train_probabilities = gmm.predict_proba(X_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add probabilities to the DataFrame\n",
        "for i in range(k):\n",
        "    X_train_df[f'probability_cluster_{i}'] = X_train_probabilities[:, i]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate probabilities for each cluster on the test set\n",
        "X_test_probabilities = gmm.predict_proba(X_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add probabilities to the DataFrame\n",
        "for i in range(k):\n",
        "    X_test_df[f'probability_cluster_{i}'] = X_test_probabilities[:, i]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize the clusters with probability values on the training set\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x='hindex', y='Cited_By', hue='cluster', data=X_train_df, palette='viridis', legend='full')\n",
        "plt.title('Clusters of Researchers with GMM Probability (Training Set)')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('hindex')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Cited_By')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Visualize the clusters with probability values on the test set\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "sns.scatterplot(x='hindex', y='Cited_By', hue='cluster', data=X_test_df, palette='viridis', legend='full')\n",
        "plt.title('Clusters of Researchers with GMM Probability (Test Set)')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('hindex')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Cited_By')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the values in the training set\n",
        "print(\"Training Set:\")\n",
        "print(X_train_df[['hindex', 'Cited_By', 'cluster', 'probability_cluster_0', 'probability_cluster_1']])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the values in the test set\n",
        "print(\"Test Set:\")\n",
        "print(X_test_df[['hindex', 'Cited_By', 'cluster', 'probability_cluster_0', 'probability_cluster_1']])"
      ],
      "metadata": {

      "cell_type": "code",

        "# Assuming 'loaded_gmm' and 'loaded_scaler' are already loaded from Google Drive\n",
        "\n",
        "# Example input for a new author's profile\n",
        "new_author_profile = {'hindex': 10, 'Cited_By': 100, 'Cited_By_5y': 90, 'h_index_5y': 1, 'i10_index': 1, 'i10_index_5y': 1}\n",
        "\n",
        "# Convert input_data to a DataFrame\n",
        "new_author_profile_df = pd.DataFrame([new_author_profile])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Standardize the new author's profile using the loaded scaler\n",
        "scaled_new_author_profile = loaded_scaler.transform(new_author_profile_df)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Use the loaded GMM model to predict the cluster for the new author\n",
        "predicted_cluster = loaded_gmm.predict(scaled_new_author_profile)\n",
